OL,3,CFrance becomes first country to
OL,4,Censhrine right to abortion in the
OL,5,Cconstitution
OL,7,FEmmanuel Macron's government voted
OL,8,Fthat Article 34 of the French
OL,9,FConstitution will be amended to
OL,10,Fspecify that "the law determines the
OL,11,Fconditions by which is exercised the
OL,12,Ffreedom of women to have recourse to
OL,13,Fan abortion, which is guaranteed."
OL,15,FBoth houses of parliament, the
OL,16,FNational Assembly and the Senate, have
OL,17,Falready adopted this - today's vote
OL,18,Fwas largely a formality.
